{
  "texts": [
    "When LLMs try to answer questions for a specific domain that is not part of the training data, hallucinations are likely.",
    "One way to address this problem is to fine-tune the LLM, which is less expensive than building a foundation model but requires considerable resources nonetheless.",
    "Studies have shown that fine-tuning can also lead to hallucinations (Gekhman et al. 2024).",
    "On the other hand, RAG is an effective way to add this knowledge.",
    "By adding additional information, questions can be answered using this data, reducing the likelihood of inaccurate answers."
  ]
}